Wiper Party leader Kalonzo Musyoka on Saturday hosted the Azimio la Umoja One Kenya presidential aspirant Raila Odinga in his Tseikuru home in Kitui County. The duo, who were joined by Kitui Governor Charity Ngilu, attended the consecration of 10 Around the Globe (ATG) Church at the Revelations City prayer park, at kwa Muthusi in Mwingi West Sub County. They are being hosted by the ATG Church Archbishop Apostle Francis Musili. Also present are the host MP Charles Nguna, and his Mwingi North, Mwingi Central and Kitui West counterparts Paul Nzengu, Gideon Mulyungi and Beth Nyenze respectively. Also at the fetes are the Kitui Senator Enoch Wambua, Kitui County women representative Irene Kasalu and former Kitui governor Julius Malombe. Raila was accompanied in his tour of Kitui by Ugunja MP Opiyo Wandayi. Before attending Bishop's consecration, Kalonzo had attended the burial of Cathryn Mbathi, the wife of a former cabinet minister Titus Mbathi at Mulango area in Kitui central sub-county.